One of a series of nine males from Mt. Humboldt, 1300 m el., 6-7-xi-2002, Monteith & Wright, lot 1076 (QMB) exhibits a broad aedeagus with a rounded tip, the ostial opening more asymmetrical apically (Fig. 
21E
), herein dubbed form Q. The other eight males of this particular collecting series all exhibit aedeagal apices similar to those from Mt. Humboldt, 1400 m (Fig. 
21C
). There are no external differences discernible among the males of this series, and no other examined male from Mt. Humboldt or anywhere else across the distributional range exhibits the "form Q" aedeagal configuration. Therefore this form is considered an infraspecific variant without nomenclatural status, with its evolutionary basis requiring further study.
